Description

As an Insurance Services/Benefits Mgmt colleague, I want the ability to override the Life and/or DI price bands assigned to a customer so they can be used in BSS for discounted pricing. To do this, we’re creating  a new Admin App page that allows HPP users to view all existing Life and DI band overrides for customers and then add/edit these pricing exceptions.

This story is for the general UI work for the new tile on Benefits Gateway 

General design of new page:

The page will be based off of other pages in the Benefits Gateway Section of Admin App pages for exceptions that are already in use, such as: Minimum Funding Exceptions, Benefit Offer Exceptions, Plan Deselection Exception. 

 

Acceptance Criteria:
Given I’m an Insurance Services colleague with access to Admin Apps > Benefits Gateway > exception pages

When I click on the Benefits Gateway link in Admin Apps

Then 

I see a new tile in the Benefits Gateway page under the “Benefits Strategy Solutions Maintenance” section

The new tiles title is “Life & Disability Band Exceptions” 

The description text on the box says: “View, edit, add, or delete Customer-level band exceptions for Life and/or Disability plans”

A Launch Now link is used to open page

When I click on the Launch Now link of the new tile

Then I am redirected to this url , /ui-bss-admin/#/LifeAndDisabilityBand-Exceptions, that opens in ui-bss-admin app 


Technical Details: 

1. No UI change needed , API will send the newly added tile in response and just test it should be displayed in UI . 
In ui-benefits repo , admin-apps-service.ts file → getAdminApps() is calling the API to get the tiles . 

2. In app.json , add a new object in “groupId” : 1001 in the end , inside “apps” array. This is to match the API response , the tile will be displayed from API response not this file.




